<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>Letter of Appointment</title>
  <style>
    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 0;
    }
    body {
    font-family: "Calibri", Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #000;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* Each PDF page */
  .page {
    width: 210mm;
    height: 297mm;
    position: relative;
    box-sizing: border-box;

    /* ✅ 25px from top, 20px from bottom */
    padding: 25px 20mm 20px 25mm;
    page-break-after: always;
  }

  /* ✅ Letterhead as full-page background */
  .letterhead {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 210mm;
    height: 297mm;
    z-index: -1;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  /* Content always stays inside safe printable area */
  .content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    text-align: justify;
    margin-top: 45mm; /* ✅ pushes text below the top logo (approx. 25px + logo zone) */
    margin-bottom: 20mm; /* ✅ ensures space above footer zone */
   
  }

  /* Headings and general formatting */
  .title {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: bold;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .date {
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  /* Address section */
  .to {
    margin-bottom: 25px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .to .name {
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .to .addr {
    white-space: normal;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    text-align: justify;
  }

  ol {
    margin-left: 20px;
    padding-left: 10px;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    text-align: justify;
  }
  /* .li .space{
    margin-left: 20px;
  } */

  /* Signature */
    .signature { margin-top: 6mm; }
      .signature .for { font-weight: 700; font-family: cambria; margin-top: -6px; }
      .signature .signer { font-weight: 300; font-family: cambria; margin-top:-9px; }
  .right {
    margin-left: 28px;
  }

  /* Annexure salary table */
  table {
        width: calc(100% - 120px);
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin: 10px 60px 12px 60px;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-family: Cambria, serif !important;
        border: 1px solid #000;
        table-layout: fixed;
      }
      th, td {
        border: 1px solid #000;
        padding: 4px 6px;
        line-height: 1.25;
        vertical-align: middle;
      }
      th {
        background: #fff;
        font-weight: bold;
        text-align: center;
        font-family: Cambria, serif !important;
        padding: 5px 6px;
      }
      th:first-child, td:first-child { text-align: left; }
      th:nth-child(2), td:nth-child(2),
      th:nth-child(3), td:nth-child(3) { text-align: right; }

    /* .note {
      font-size: 11px;
      margin-top: 18px;
      width: 80%;
      margin-left: auto;
      
    } */
    .annexure-title{
      text-align: center;
    }

    /* .note ul {
      margin-top: 6px;
      margin-left: 20px;
    } */

    /* === Ensure each page bottom spacing === */
    .page::after {
      content: "";
      display: block;
      height: 20px;
    }

    .page-break {
      page-break-after: always;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <!-- ===== PAGE 1 ===== -->
  <div class="page">
    <% if (letterheadPath) { %>
      <img src="<%= letterheadPath %>" class="letterhead" alt="Letterhead" />
    <% } %>

    <div class="content">
      <p class="date"><% 
        const dateStr = appointment.issueDate || appointment.appointmentDate || ""; 
        if (dateStr) { 
          let formattedDate = '';
          if (dateStr instanceof Date) {
            const day = String(dateStr.getDate()).padStart(2, '0');
            const month = String(dateStr.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, '0');
            const year = dateStr.getFullYear();
            formattedDate = `${day}-${month}-${year}`;
          } else if (typeof dateStr === 'string') {
            const [year, month, day] = dateStr.split('-');
            formattedDate = `${day}-${month}-${year}`;
          }
      %><%= formattedDate %><% } %></p>

      <p class="title">Letter of Appointment</p>

      <div class="to">
        <p>To,</p>
        <p class="name"><%= appointment.employeeName || "" %>,</p>
        <%
          const address = appointment.address || '';
          const parts = address.split(/[,;\n]+/).map(p => p.trim()).filter(Boolean);
          let formatted = [];
          if (parts.length <= 3) {
            formatted = parts;
          } else if (parts.length === 4) {
            formatted = [parts.slice(0, 2).join(', '), parts[2], parts[3]];
          } else {
            formatted = [parts.slice(0, 2).join(', '), parts.slice(2, 4).join(', '), parts.slice(4).join(', ')];
          }
        %>
        <p class="addr">
          <% formatted.forEach(function(line, index){ %>
            <%= line %><% if (index < formatted.length - 1) { %>,<% } %><br/>
          <% }) %>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>Dear <%= appointment.employeeName || "" %>,</p>

      <p><strong>Sub: Your Career with AMAZON IT SOLUTIONS.</strong></p>

      <p>We are immensely pleased to appoint you as a <strong><%= appointment.position || appointment.designation || "" %></strong>, and have you as a part of Amazon IT Solutions Family. We believe your potential skills will be a valuable contribution to our company.</p>

      <p><strong> Effective Date of Appointment:</strong> Your Date of Joining at <strong>"Amazon IT Solutions"</strong> is <% 
        const joiningDateStr = appointment.joiningDate || ""; 
        if (joiningDateStr) { 
          let formattedJoiningDate = '';
          if (joiningDateStr instanceof Date) {
            const day = String(joiningDateStr.getDate()).padStart(2, '0');
            const month = String(joiningDateStr.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, '0');
            const year = joiningDateStr.getFullYear();
            formattedJoiningDate = `${day}-${month}-${year}`;
          } else if (typeof joiningDateStr === 'string') {
            const [year, month, day] = joiningDateStr.split('-');
            formattedJoiningDate = `${day}-${month}-${year}`;
          }
      %><%= formattedJoiningDate %><% } %> and following are the terms and conditions:</p>

      <ol>
        <li><strong> Job Assignment:</strong>In your assignment, you will be required to perform duties as laid down in the Job Description for your position.</li>
        <li><strong> Leave Entitlement:</strong>You will be entitled to leaves as per the Amazon IT Solutions policy mentioned in the Rules and Regulations formulated in the Employee Handbook of Amazon IT Solutions from time to time.</li>
        <li><strong> Placement & Compensation:</strong> You will be placed in the appropriate responsibility level of the Company and will be entitled to total compensation of <strong>INR <%= appointment.ctcAnnual ? Number(appointment.ctcAnnual).toLocaleString('en-IN') : "" %> (<%= appointment.ctcWords || "" %>)</strong> Per Annum. Compensation will be governed by the rules of the Company, as applicable and/or amended hereafter.</li>
      </ol>

      <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Note: Breakup of the fixed salary is as per the Annexure sheet.</p>

      <ol start="4">
        <li><strong>Statutory Deductions:</strong> Deductions, if any, will be made from your salary as per the prevailing law of the country. However, for your income tax you shall be personally responsible for filing returns etc. The company will provide you with the tax, deductions certificate, if applicable, at the end of each financial year.</li>
        <li><strong>Code of Conduct:</strong> The Code of Business Conduct and Ethics helps to ensure compliance with 
legal requirements and our standards as approved by the Board from time to time,formulated in 
the Employee Handbook of Amazon IT solutions. All employees are expected to read and understand 
this Code of Business Conduct and Ethics, uphold these standards in day-to-day activities, comply 
with all applicable policies and procedures, and adhere to these standards. 
</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== PAGE 2 ===== -->
  <div class="page">
    <% if (letterheadPath) { %><img src="<%= letterheadPath %>" class="letterhead" /><% } %>
    <div class="content">
      <ol start="6">
