        <li>
          <p style="text-align: justify;">
  <strong>Termination of employment:</strong>
</p>
<p style="margin-left: 20px; text-align: justify;">
  13.1 During the probationary period and any extension thereof, services can be terminated by either party
  by giving two months' notice in writing or gross salary in lieu thereof, only by the employer and this does
  not apply for the employee. However, on confirmation the services can be terminated by either party by giving
  Ninety Days (90 days) notice in writing or gross salary in lieu thereof, only by the employer and this does not
  apply for the employee. Buying out of notice period is up to the sole discretion of the management.
</p>
  
</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== PAGE 3 ===== -->
  <div class="page">
    <% if (letterheadPath) { %><img src="<%= letterheadPath %>" class="letterhead" /><% } %>
    <div class="content">
      <h4 style="margin-left:10px;">Discretion of the management:</h4>
<p style="margin-left: 50px; text-align: justify;">
  13.2 Upon termination of employment, you will immediately hand over to the Company all correspondence,
  specifications, formulae, books, documents, market data, cost data, drawings, effects, or records belonging to
  the Company or relating to its business and shall not retain or make copies of these items.
</p>

<p style="margin-left: 50px; text-align: justify;">
  13.3 Upon termination of employment, you will also return all company property which may be in your possession.
</p>
<ol start="14">
        <li><strong>General Conditions:</strong> You will be bound by the following: </li>

<p style="margin-left: 20px; text-align: justify;">14.1 You will not engage in any unlawful or any subversive activity while in the service of
"amazon IT solutions".</p>
<p style="margin-left: 20px; text-align: justify;">14.2 Amazon IT solutions will expect you to work in section/department/process/project
in which you are placed with a high standard of initiative, efficiency and economy. </p>
<p style="margin-left: 20px; text-align: justify;">14.3 You shall not, under any circumstances either directly or indirectly, receive or accept
for own benefit any commission, rebate, discount, gift or profit of any nature from any
